During the Huawei presentation, the slides mentioned Mate 10 series has a 30% improvement in battery life over the Mate 9. However when looking at the breakdown of official battery stats listed on their shopping site for the Mate 10 atleast, the increase in not uniformly distributed. 
 
Mate 9 
3G call: up to 30 hours;  
4G web browsing: up to 20 hours;  
Video playback: up to 20 hours;  
audio playback: up Up to 105 hours;  
standby time: up to 21 days; 
 
Mate 10 
3G call: 25 hours; 
4G web browsing: 21 hours; 
Video playback: 20 hours; 
audio playback: 160 hours; 
standby time: up to 22 days;
 
So in all the Mate 9 to Mate 10 upgrade will give a minor boost in battery in real life usage depending on the your tasks. The efficiency of Kirin 970 is balanced out by the QHD display and additional 4 cores on the GPU. No breaking records to be expected.
